ng, Marilyn French, Marge Piercy, Alix Kates Shulman, Alison Lurie, Joanna Russ, and Joan Didion--Hogeland explores the ways in which consciousness-raising novels addressed some of the most important questions raised by second-wave feminism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAmerican fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aFeminism and literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aFeminist fiction, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aGroup identity in literature. 0aInterpersonal relations in literature. 0aWomen and literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Feminist.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999 (pre Pub)z97831104425260 cprintz978081223429940uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151280415740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512804157423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781512804157.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  Penn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK